    "reasoning": "1) Convert hard drive capacity to MB. Given 1 GB = 1024 MB and the drive is 300 GB, total capacity C in MB is C = 300 × 1024 = 307200 MB. 2) Define d = C − 307100. Substitute C = 307200 to get d = 307200 − 307100 = 100. 3) Storage space remaining: Julia puts 300000 MB on the drive, so remaining empty space is 307200 − 300000 = 7200 MB. This value, however, is not directly needed for the later percent savings expression; the problem only uses d in the percentage formula. 4) Bicycle and helmet sale details: Regular bicycle price = $320; 20% off means savings of 0.20 × 320 = 64, so sale price is 320 − 64 = 256. Regular helmet price = $80; 10% off means savings of 0.10 × 80 = 8, so sale price is 80 − 8 = 72. 5) Total savings and total regular price: Total savings = 64 + 8 = 72. Total regular price (total price in the denominator) = 320 + 80 = 400. 6) Sandra’s percentage savings without the d factor would be (total savings / total price) × 100% = (72 / 400) × 100% = 18%. 7) The problem defines Sandra’s percentage savings on the total purchase as ((total savings) / (total price)) × d%. We already have total savings / total price = 72 / 400 = 0.18, and d = 100, so this becomes 0.18 × 100% = 18%. 8) Therefore, the requested computed value is 18.",
    "answer": "18"
